{"article_id":"xdV7viC8GWIDScIG","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Update , 10 p.m . ET :","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"After more than nine hours and 30 minutes , Internet service has been restored in North Korea ,","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"according to technology news service Dyn Research .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Access is only partial ,","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Reuters reports ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"but the country 's main news service and newspaper both are back online .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"Original post :","depth":3},{"id":7,"text":"North Korea 's Internet is offline","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"- days after President Obama pledged a `` proportional response '' to the communist country 's alleged hacking of Sony Pictures ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"multiple news reports say .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Doug Madory , the director of Internet analysis at Dyn Research , told The New York Times and other news organizations","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"that North Korea 's Internet access became unstable late Friday .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"By Monday , it was offline ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"San Francisco-based CloudFlare , a network and security company","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"that monitors global Web access ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"told The Times","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"that North Korea 's Internet access was `` toast . ''","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"It 's unclear what caused the outage ,","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"but State Department spokeswoman Marie Harf said today :","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"`` We are n't going to discuss publicly operational details about the possible response options","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"or comment on those kind of reports in any way","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"except to say","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"that","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"as we implement our responses ,","depth":14},{"id":25,"text":"some will be seen ,","depth":15},{"id":26,"text":"some may not be seen . ''","depth":15},{"id":27,"text":"In an interview with NPR 's Elise Hu , Matthew Prince , chief executive of CloudFlare , pointed to four possible scenarios :","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"North Korea turned off its own Internet ;","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"China 's upstream provider turned it off ;","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"the country 's routers failed at an unfortunate time ;","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"or it was the result of a denial-of-service attack from either a hacking group or the U.S .","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"Prince said","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"he thinks","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"it 's unlikely the U.S. was behind the reported outage .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"North Korea has one of the lowest Internet penetrations in the world","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"with access limited mostly to the country 's elite .","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"The U.S. has linked the recent hacking of Sony Pictures to North Korean hackers ,","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"though North Korea itself has denied","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"it is responsible -","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"even though it called the act righteous .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"There are computer security experts","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"who question","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"whether Pyongyang is behind the hack .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"Last week , Sony canceled the planned Christmas Day release of The Interview , a comedy","depth":4},{"id":46,"text":"that centers on a plot","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"to assassinate North Korean leader Kim Jong Un .","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"The decision followed threats against moviegoers and theaters","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"that showed the film .","depth":5},{"id":50,"text":"The threats were attributed to the group","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"that claimed responsibility","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"for hacking Sony .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":105,"